cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper focuses on developing a graph-based Tree Adjoining Grammar (TAG) parser using neural networks for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper extensively uses neural networks, including BiLSTMs, highway connections, and character-level CNNs, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to alleviate the trade-off between transition-based and graph-based parsing systems, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using convolutional neural networks for character-level embeddings, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
